pageContext.claim: ““We had people working three jobs, two jobs, and they were doing worse than they did 20 years ago. That’s not happening anymore.”
pageContext.analysis: During the 2016 campaign, Trump would repeatedly claim people had to work two ot three jobs to make ends meet or pay for Obamacare. But the percentage of workers holding two or more job has barely changed between 2016 and 2018; it has remained about five percent.
